        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 2:34PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 233 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southwest of Mount Auburn, or 16 miles north of Taylorville,
moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Illiopolis, Niantic, and Mount Auburn.

This includes Interstate 72 between mile markers 117 and 127.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Lincoln.</instruction>
